<article title='Colorado_Front_Range'><paragraph><template><target>unreferenced</target><arg name="date">June 2009</arg><arg name="bot">yes</arg></template><template><target>main</target><arg>Geography of Colorado</arg></template>The<space/><bold>Colorado Front Range</bold><space/>is a colloquial geographic term for the most populous region of the state of<space/><link><target>Colorado</target></link><space/>in the<space/><link><target>United States</target></link>. The area is located just east of the<space/><link><target>foothills</target></link><space/>of the<space/><link><target>Front Range</target></link>, aligned in a north-south configuration on the western edge of the<space/><link><target>Great Plains</target></link>, where they meet the Rockies.<space/><link><target>Geology</target><part>Geologically</part></link>, the region lies mostly within the<space/><link><target>Colorado Piedmont</target></link>, in the valley of the<space/><link><target>South Platte River</target><part>South Platte</part></link><space/>and<space/><link><target>Arkansas River</target><part>Arkansas</part></link><space/>rivers on the east side of the Rockies. The region contains the largest cities and the majority of the population of Colorado.</paragraph><paragraph>The Colorado Front Range communities include (in a roughly north-to-south order):</paragraph><list type='bullet'><listitem><link><target>Fort Collins, Colorado</target><part>Fort Collins</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Greeley, Colorado</target><part>Greeley</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Loveland, Colorado</target><part>Loveland</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Longmont, Colorado</target><part>Longmont</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Boulder, Colorado</target><part>Boulder</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Golden, Colorado</target><part>Golden</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Denver-Aurora Metropolitan Area</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Castle Rock, Colorado</target><part>Castle Rock</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Colorado Springs, Colorado</target><part>Colorado Springs</part></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Pueblo, Colorado</target><part>Pueblo</part></link></listitem></list><paragraph>The addition of the adjacent<space/><link><target>Wyoming</target></link><space/>city of<space/><link><target>Cheyenne, Wyoming</target><part>Cheyenne</part></link><space/>to the Colorado Front Range forms the full<space/><link><target>Front Range Urban Corridor</target></link>.</paragraph><heading level='2'>See also</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem><link><target>Colorado metropolitan areas</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Front Range</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Front Range Urban Corridor</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Geography of Colorado</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>State of Colorado</target></link></listitem></list><paragraph><template><target>Colorado</target><arg>expand</arg></template></paragraph><paragraph><template><target>Coord</target><arg>40.5</arg><arg>-105</arg><arg>scale:1000000</arg><arg name="display">title</arg></template></paragraph><paragraph><link><target>Category:Regions of Colorado</target></link><link><target>Category:Tourism regions of Colorado</target></link></paragraph><paragraph><template><target>Colorado-stub</target></template></paragraph></article>